http://www.json.org/ shows that the string of a {string:value} pair inside an object must have quotes around it, yet your api isn't following that (see your example above) - and that's causing PHP's json_decode function to return NULL.

{ name: “Joe Doe”, title: “VP, Engineering”, phone: “13-456-7890?}  should be

{ "name": “Joe Doe”, "title": “VP, Engineering”, "phone": “13-456-7890?}

It is all click jacking and we might see more such attacks in future.

The quickest fix for this attack is - DO NOT let your site be loaded in an iframe. Thats it!

if (window.parent.frames.length>0) {
//you are framed.
//Go to your site without frame
window.parent.location=location;
}

